
[1]sadden

   SADDEN, v.t. sad'n.

   1. To make sad or sorrowful; also, to make melancholy or gloomy.

   2. To make dark colored. Obs.

   3. To make heavy, firm or cohesive.

   Marl is binding, and saddening of land is the great prejudice it doth
   to clay lands. Obs.
